---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="The team behind Eat for Life — empowerment eating, no rules, all appetite."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-02-28')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<style>
		.about-intro {
			margin-bottom: 2.5em;
		}
		.contributors {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
			gap: 2em;
			margin-top: 2em;
		}
		.contributor {
			border: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
			border-radius: 12px;
			padding: 1.5em;
			text-align: center;
		}
		.contributor img {
			width: 100px;
			height: 100px;
			border-radius: 50%;
			object-fit: cover;
			margin-bottom: 1em;
			background: rgb(var(--gray-light));
		}
		.contributor h3 {
			margin: 0 0 0.25em;
			font-size: 1.1em;
		}
		.contributor .role {
			font-size: 0.85em;
			color: rgb(var(--gray));
			margin-bottom: 0.75em;
			font-style: italic;
		}
		.contributor p {
			font-size: 0.9em;
			margin: 0;
		}
		.coming-soon {
			opacity: 0.55;
		}
		.coming-soon .role::after {
			content: " · coming soon";
			font-weight: bold;
			color: rgb(var(--accent));
		}
	</style>

	<div class="about-intro">
		<p>
			<strong>Eat for Life</strong> is a food blog about eating with intention — not rules. No calorie counting, no wellness trends, no sponsored spirulina. Just honest writing about what food actually is: memory, culture, medicine, pleasure, and occasionally a disaster in a wok.
		</p>
		<p>
			The blog grows out of a longer obsession with how food, science, history and daily life intersect — an obsession that also lives over at <a href="https://www.drgichao.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">drgichao.com</a>, where the same restless curiosity gets applied to everything from gut biology to the economics of the Silk Road.
		</p>
		<p>
			Here, the focus is the table. Pull up a chair.
		</p>
	</div>

	<h2>The Team</h2>

	<div class="contributors">

		<div class="contributor">
			<img src="/placeholder-avatar.png" alt="FlyingGG" onerror="this.style.background='#e8e0d5';this.removeAttribute('src')" />
			<h3>FlyingGG</h3>
			<div class="role">Founder & Admin</div>
			<p>
				Pilot-trained, perpetually curious, and deeply suspicious of any food trend that requires a subscription. Writes about the gut-brain axis, comfort food politics, and the kind of Tuesday congee that makes you feel like a person again. Also found at <a href="https://www.drgichao.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">drgichao.com</a>.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="contributor coming-soon">
			<img src="/placeholder-avatar.png" alt="IndianaJen the Foodie" onerror="this.style.background='#e8e0d5';this.removeAttribute('src')" />
			<h3>IndianaJen the Foodie</h3>
			<div class="role">Food Explorer</div>
			<p>
				[Placeholder: IndianaJen has eaten in places you'd need a map and a very good excuse to find. Bio incoming — she's still finishing a bowl of something remarkable.]
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="contributor coming-soon">
			<img src="/placeholder-avatar.png" alt="Meatlover" onerror="this.style.background='#e8e0d5';this.removeAttribute('src')" />
			<h3>Meatlover</h3>
			<div class="role">Carnivore Correspondent</div>
			<p>
				[Placeholder: Meatlover has strong opinions about fire, fat, and the correct internal temperature of a ribeye. We've been promised a bio. We're waiting. So is the steak.]
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="contributor coming-soon">
			<img src="/placeholder-avatar.png" alt="The Decanted Diva" onerror="this.style.background='#e8e0d5';this.removeAttribute('src')" />
			<h3>The Decanted Diva</h3>
			<div class="role">Wine & Glamour</div>
			<p>
				[Placeholder: Former beauty queen. Current wine empress. The Decanted Diva once wore a crown; now she wears a very good Burgundy. Her palate detects terroir the way others detect drama — effortlessly, and usually correctly.]
			</p>
		</div>

	</div>
</Layout>
